The political institutions, even if they were formally founded correctly, remain only sham buildings behind which the patriarchal relations will continue to grow.
The balancing of interests between the different ethnic groups is unusually complicated, especially because of the unclearness of the circumstances that further complicate the influences of Pakistan and Iran.
The building of a “capable state,” which is the minimalist goal of the whole operation, is also very unrealistic.
Time horizon of Obama’s strategy astounded by his voluntarism
