Vaccination against pneumococcal disease free and voluntary
Vaccination against pneumococcal bacteria changes the usual from January.
It should be the first to be free and voluntary for families.
But already now, votes are reporting that mandatory vaccination would be more effective.
The preparations for the introduction of the free vaccination against pneumococcus culminate.
The Pharmaceutical Institute already sets the maximum prices for the vaccines that health insurance must pay.
