Some see images in a waking state and hear voices that others do not see or hear.
It is not only in mentally ill people and drug addiction that the boundaries between imagination and reality are blurred.
As long as it happens in your sleep, everything is fine.
When we lie in our dark rooms with our eyes closed, we are allowed to indulge unrestrained in the wildest ideas and imaginations.
However, those who experience traumatic conditions in waking, seeing and hearing things that others do not see or hear, in the modern Western world are usually considered crazy or drug addicts, at least as specialties.
