Why exactly our brain beats capriolen, researchers still pose puzzles.
Exceptional conditions can cause any person to temporarily lose the reference to reality, Fuchs says.
But not everyone will develop psychosis.
There seems to be a genetic predisposition to schizophrenia, but twin studies have shown that the genes are not the determining factors alone.
Researchers assume that there is minimal brain damage in those affected.
