How Much Should You Earn From Your Facebook Profile?
Facebook users can now, thanks to the new application Trovit, the search engine with the most ads of real estate, job offers and cars in Spain, learn their salary that they should earn based on their profile.
The "How much should you earn?" tool calculates the salaries of users based on more than 140,000 job vacancies available at Trovit in Spain. Users are provided with a form on Facebook to enter their profession, work experience, age and the city in which they work.
Already a week after the application became available for the first time, the search engine found that the Spanish worker on average "feels badly paid", explains Albert Ribera, responsible for the product Trovit, in a press release.
The Spaniards are the lowest paid according to the data that Trovit has through its search engines in the United Kingdom and France.
A British programmer receives a gross annual salary of 45,226 euros and a Frenchman 31,059 euros, in contrast to the 24,000 euros earned by a Spaniard.
As a result, a truck driver has an annual net salary of 34,247 euros in England, 25,751 in France and 16,420 euros in Spain.
According to Trovit, the lowest-paid work in Spain is that of a waiter with 11.592 euros per year net, followed by the work of a salesman with 14.725 euros and that of a worker with 15.667 euros.
The most searched jobs on the Internet in the last three months are those of a driver, half-day jobs and social worker.
